05:28.397 --> 05:40.015
It's a little bit unusual because they've put the first verse as therefore a weird way to start a book because it therefore refers to whatever was before it.

05:40.836 --> 05:47.506
So we have to look at the last verse in 1 Peter 3, 22, which says,

05:48.674 --> 05:59.545
who has gone, and this is, speaking of Jesus, who has gone into heaven and is at God's right hand with angels, authorities, powers, and submission to Him.

05:59.585 --> 06:01.767
Amen, that's where our Savior is today.

06:03.529 --> 06:16.242
So first Peter 4-1 begins, therefore, since Christ suffered in His body, arm yourself also with the same attitude because whoever suffers

06:16.578 --> 06:18.441
in the body is done with sin.

06:19.863 --> 06:22.207
So here, right off the bat, we're armed.

06:22.707 --> 06:23.328
We're warned.

06:24.851 --> 06:32.983
When we arm ourselves with his attitude, there's going to be some suffering, and we see suffering all over the world now.

06:35.768 --> 06:39.613
Satan is attacking us any time, any way he can.

06:40.435 --> 06:42.398
He hates us when we follow Christ.

06:43.539 --> 06:45.202
