06:45.762 --> 06:48.887
to provoke fear, doubt, and make us anxious.

06:49.628 --> 06:51.992
The men on Wednesday night were studying a book.

06:52.252 --> 07:00.886
It's been a blessing called calm moments in anxious days, a perfect topic for what we're going through now all over the world.

07:00.926 --> 07:04.872
And then he talks about the attitude of Christ.

07:04.992 --> 07:07.616
So how do we obtain that attitude?

07:09.880 --> 07:14.066
Paul explains some of the points on Christ's attitude and Philippians.

07:15.170 --> 07:28.407
He says, Christ was God in heaven, but did not use that status to benefit himself, but rather became a servant and became like an ordinary human.

07:29.589 --> 07:32.412
He served others, but not himself.

07:34.114 --> 07:35.556
He also humbled himself.

07:36.237 --> 07:43.186
Look how he was born in that danger, that trough, feeding trough, not in a palace, not royalty,

07:43.970 --> 07:45.331
He was born to poor parents.

07:47.193 --> 07:50.496
He never retaliated when they beat him and mocked him.

07:50.556 --> 07:51.897
He never retaliated.

07:51.937 --> 07:54.340
How did he go into Jerusalem?

07:55.801 --> 08:00.125
He went in on a donkey, not on a large white horse fit for a king.

08:02.788 --> 08:08.973
He was like a lamb going to the slaughter, as it says in Isaiah, silent before the shearers.

08:10.154 --> 08:11.916
I can understand the sheep doing that.

08:11.976 --> 08:13.938
The sheep didn't know what they were in for.

08:14.466 --> 08:17.590
But Jesus did and he chose to do it anyway.

08:21.936 --> 08:26.783
And to his executioners, he said, forgive them for they do not know what they are doing.

08:28.265 --> 08:32.471
So that's Paul's second point was being humble.

08:32.531 --> 08:34.654
We should humble ourselves as Christ did.

08:35.756 --> 08:43.186
The word says, for all those who exalt themselves will be humbled and those

08:43.522 --> 08:46.086
who humble themselves will be exalted.

08:46.286 --> 08:46.967
That's beautiful.

08:47.869 --> 08:50.573
In the world, we do everything exact opposite.

08:50.753 --> 09:02.071
We exalt celebrities, important people, billionaires, and we kind of trod down on the humble and forget about them.

09:03.594 --> 09:05.917
And the Lord was completely obedient.

09:08.101 --> 09:11.346
So obedient that He showed His sacrificial love

09:12.674 --> 09:19.605
And that is important because Jesus a couple times says he wants all of us, not just part of us.

09:19.645 --> 09:25.094
He wants all of our heart, all of our attention as an acceptable sacrifice.

09:27.117 --> 09:28.920
The word says he is a jealous God.

09:29.000 --> 09:32.646
He doesn't want anything else to take half of us away.

09:33.707 --> 09:37.053
He wants our total worship and total commitment.

09:38.175 --> 09:40.338
And to that cross, he went willingly

09:40.802 --> 09:49.277
knowing that he would be mocked, whipped, insulted, spit on, had his beard pulled out, beaten and crucified.

09:51.020 --> 09:53.445
So that's a good time to do a self-check.

09:53.785 --> 09:56.009
How are we on obedience?

09:58.073 --> 10:02.962
Paul wrote, I want to see if you would stand the test and be obedient in everything.

10:04.034 --> 10:07.379
It's easy to be obedient when something is on our will.

10:07.559 --> 10:08.781
Oh, I totally support that.

10:08.841 --> 10:10.023
I'm gonna be obedient here.

10:10.063 --> 10:11.144
That's the easy part.

10:11.705 --> 10:17.113
But how are we when the Lord tells us and it's His will to do something we don't wanna do?

10:17.133 --> 10:19.816
That's kind of the test of this thing.

10:20.437 --> 10:21.559
Are we ingredient there?

10:21.579 --> 10:25.745
